  "slug": "tikoy-nian-gao-recip",
  "name": "Tikoy Recipe",
  "recipe_type": "dessert",
  "brief_description": "Tikoy or Ni\u00e1n g\u0101o is a type of rice cake made from glutinous rice flour and considered as a centerpiece during Chinese New Year. This is also popularly known as Chinese New Year pudding.",
  "cuisine": null,
  "instructions": [
    {
      "position": 1,
      "text": "Combine water and brown sugar then mix well"
    },
    {
      "position": 2,
      "text": "Combine glutinous rice flour with the water and brown sugar mixture then mix thoroughly."
    },
    {
      "position": 3,
      "text": "Add the pitted chopped dates then mix until every ingredient is well distributed."
    },
    {
      "position": 4,
      "text": "Grease a round cake pan and transfer the glutinous rice flour mixture then sprinkle the sesame seeds on top."
    },
    {
      "position": 5,
      "text": "Steam for 45 minutes. Make sure to cover the top part with cheesecloth to avoid water drippings."
    },
    {
      "position": 6,
      "text": "Remove the tikoy from the cake pan and transfer to a wax paper or cling wrap then refrigerate for at least 5 hours. Take the tikoy out of the refrigerator. Cook using your desired method.It can be re-steamed, microwaved, or fried after dipping in beaten egg mixture."
    }
  ],
  "servings": 6,
  "cooking_time_minutes": 45,
